parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement, which can leave the driver stranded and pose a safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Sludge Buildup
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of sludge in the engine can cause premature engine failure, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement, which can leave the driver stranded and pose a safety risk.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become undriveable, leading to costly repairs or even transmission replacement, which can leave the driver stranded and pose a safety risk.
The sudden shut down of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded, especially on high-speed roads like freeways.
symptoms: The engine dies or shuts down while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The strange knocking and screeching noise when changing gears can indicate a faulty transmission, which can lead to transmission failure, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, and potentially resulting in accidents.
